# Global Docs Validation Procedure

Last updated: 2026-06-04

Scope: `/opt/Axodus/.instructions`

Status: REQ-01 recovery artifact for Global Docs / Instructions L1 to L2.

This procedure validates documentation presence and safety boundaries only. It does not validate runtime behavior and does not authorize production execution.

## Required Safe Validation

Run from `/opt/Axodus`:

```bash
cd /opt/Axodus
test -d .instructions
test -f .instructions/NUCLEUS_MATURITY_FRAMEWORK.md
test -f .instructions/NUCLEUS_MATURITY_REGISTER.md
test -f .instructions/PORTFOLIO_STATUS.md
test -f .instructions/PORTFOLIO_ROADMAP.md
test -f .instructions/BLOCKER_REGISTER.md
test -f .instructions/PORTFOLIO_REQUEST_QUEUE.md
test -f .instructions/PORTFOLIO_SPRINT_01_ALLOCATION.md
test -f .instructions/GLOBAL_DOCS_SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md
test -f .instructions/GLOBAL_DOCS_OWNERSHIP.md
test -f .instructions/GLOBAL_DOCS_VERSIONING_STRATEGY.md
test -f .instructions/GLOBAL_DOCS_VALIDATION.md
find .instructions -maxdepth 2 -type f | sort
git status --short --branch || true
```

Expected root Git result:

```text
fatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git
```

This is expected until a coordinator-approved versioning decision is executed.

## Optional Safe Checks

Optional boundary search:

```bash
grep -R "DISABLED" .instructions/GLOBAL_DOCS_*.md .instructions/PORTFOLIO_STATUS.md .instructions/BLOCKER_REGISTER.md
```

Optional Markdown inspection:

```bash
find .instructions -maxdepth 2 -type f -name "*.md" | sort
```

Only use external markdown linters if already installed and known safe. Do not install packages to run lint.

## Forbidden Validation Commands

Do not run:

```bash
git init
git add
git commit
git reset
git clean
npm install
pnpm install
yarn install
npm run build
pnpm run build
yarn build
npm test
pnpm test
yarn test
docker compose up
forge test
hardhat test
anvil
deploy scripts
migration scripts
trading scripts
swap scripts
settlement scripts
wallet scripts
```

Also forbidden:

- repository restructuring;
- deleting reports;
- moving global docs;
- starting services;
- connecting to external APIs;
- reading or writing secrets;
- production config changes;
- runtime execution;
- wallet signing;
- on-chain writes;
- trading, swaps, settlement, treasury, or payout commands.

## L2 Exit Criteria

Global Docs / Instructions reaches L2 candidate/validated state when:

- source-of-truth policy exists;
- ownership policy exists;
- versioning strategy exists;
- validation procedure exists;
- blocker register records unresolved repository/versioning decision;
- required files pass existence validation;
- root non-Git status is documented;
- no runtime behavior changed;
- no repository restructuring occurred;
- production/execution status remains DISABLED.

## Failure Handling

If a required file is missing:

1. Do not infer L2.
2. Record the missing file in the report.
3. Create or update only the approved documentation artifact.
4. Rerun required file validation.

If root Git status unexpectedly succeeds:

1. Do not stage or commit.
2. Inspect only with read-only commands.
3. Record the changed root Git state in the report.
4. Request coordinator decision before using root Git.

## L2 Evidence

This validation procedure is required evidence for Global Docs / Instructions L2. Passing it shows the global docs recovery baseline is documented and checkable; it does not resolve formal versioning.
